1998 but was expected to reopen.<ref>{{Cite news |author=Jack Encarnacao |publication-date=January 9, 2012 |title=Births to return to Quincy Medical Center |newspaper=[[The Patriot Ledger]] |url=http://www.patriotledger.com/features/x1266412669/Births-to-return-to-Quincy-Medical-Center |accessdate=September 25, 2012 }}</ref>  The remainder of the hospital was closed on December 26, 2014 after receiving a waiver from the department of health of the 90-day public notification rule. \n\nIt was originally scheduled to close December 31, 2014 despite a legal agreement with the state's attorney general's office it made when purchasing the hospital from bankruptcy in 2011 which stated it would not close the hospital before 2017.  Steward did agree to maintain an emergency room open under the license of Carney Hospital, Steward's facility in Dorchester in an off site location until the end of 2015.  Any inpatient care would be transferred to other hospitals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/business/2014/12/26/quincy-medical-center-closes-its-doors-midnight/tU9GOvwImj8n7S1qmz8goN/story.html|title=Quincy Medical Center closes its doors at midnight|author=Priyanka Dayal|website=BostonGlobe.com|accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nBrook Thurston, a spokesman from Steward Health Care System, responded to the controversy that Steward plans to close Quincy Medical stating \"North Adams and Radius (which Steward owned) gave virtually no notice and no transition plan.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.patriotledger.com/article/20141107/News/141106959|title=Quincy mayor questions legality of hospital closure|first=Patrick|last=Ronan|newspaper=The Patriot Ledger|accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nQuincy, a city of over 90,000 people, has become the largest city in Massachusetts without a hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/business/2014/11/06/steward-shut-down-quincy-medical-center-largest-massachusetts-hospital-closure-decade/bVl0qPstKwouQLMKQ3UJiI/story.html|title=Quincy Medical Center to close|author=Priyanka Dayal|website=BostonGlobe.com|accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wcvb.com/article/quincy-medical-center-to-shut-down/8211307|title=Quincy Medical Center to shut down|date=6 November 2014|website=Wcvb.com|accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://boston.cbslocal.com/2014/11/06/quincy-medical-center-to-close-dec-31/|title=Quincy Medical Center To Close Dec. 31|date=6 November 2014|website=Boston.cbslocal.com|accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080315070150/http://www.quincymc.org/ Official site]\n\n[[Category:Hospitals in Norfolk County, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Quincy, Massachusetts]]\n\n\n{{Massachusetts-hospital-stub}}\n{{authority control}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox hospital\n<!-- All parameters and comments should be left intact for future editors -->\n<!-- All parameters are optional, but please copy the entire template -->\n<!-- Full documentation: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Infobox_hospital -->\n| name        = Quincy Medical Center\n| org/group   = [[Steward Health Care System]]\n| logo        = <!-- please conform to copyright -->\n| logo_size   = <!-- logo size or width in pixels -->\n| image       = <!-- preferably photo of the main building or entrance -->\n| image_size  = <!-- 220 is the default image size or width in pixels (225 matches default map_size). Leave blank per [[MOS:ACCESSIBILITY]] unless special size is needed. -->\n| alt         = <!-- alternative text for image, see [[WP:ALT]] -->\n| caption     = <!-- text displayed below image -->\n| map_type    = <!-- uses the [[Template:Location map]] format; defines value for {{{1}}} parameter; must have latitude and longitude if using this -->\n| relief      = <!-- any non-blank value (yes, 1, etc.) will cause the template to display a relief map image, where available -->\